Good maude, we've gone over this time and again at BC! A clone doesn't equal the same person (as already stated). It's all so &quot;Pet Sematery&quot;! <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Madonna...spends most of &quot;Swept Away&quot; in a black bikini, which isn't an entirely bad thing, considering how hard she works on her body. If only her belly button could talk! Then we wouldn't have to listen to her voice.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ~ Salon Review</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tinlizzy@religiousdebate60574>TinLizzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#3333ff>(12/29/02 7:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Great question Em</span><hr size=1> Hi Em!<br>
<br>
OK, I'll bite as a religious person (though some we know would debate that label <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  Yes, I believe a cloned person would have a soul.  Why?  Because a person is a person, no matter how he or she got here.  Of course, I also like to believe my cat has a soul.<br>
<br>
I do have a problem with cloning--I don't think we should do something just because it's scientifically possible.  I have no issue with anything that truly improves lives, I just don't see this as one of them.  Plus, it weirds me out.  Who knows if this latest claim is real--but if it's not, I feel it's only a matter of time.<br>
<br>
My main issue right now is that cloning is not a perfected procedure and I don't like the idea of experimenting on humans.  I've read articles about the high number cloning disasters on mammals--freakish things that I can't believe someone would risk inflicting on their child.  There are other ways to have children, if you so desire.<br>
<br>
So, that's my .02 for what it's worth.<br>
<br>
