<br>
A clone would be just like a twin of you. Now, as a twin (but only a fraternal twin) I got to know alot of other twins, a number of them identical. Even have a couple of identical twins in the family as well. These are children in the womb at the same time - can't get any more similar than that now can you? Yet when they are born, they already show different personalities. Hell, they show them in the womb as well. Of all the twins I know, I can think of only one set who were even remotely alike, and even they had their differences. <br>
<br>
As for a soul. IF (big IF) there are souls, and since I do believe there is a higher something, just not what they think of as god, then clones would have one. Why wouldn't they? I've tried to think of a reason why it wouldn't have a soul and I can't think of one. If souls are given, then surely a benevolent G-d would give this baby a soul as well. If souls split apart from the souls of those creating it, then it would have part of the soul of its mother -ok that's a little creepy. So why wouldn't it have a soul?<br>
<br>
Of course my lovely MIL is saying SOULLESS there for its one of the signs of the apopcolipse (sp). Then again, she's been shouting that one for a long time. She hasn't even started saving for retirement because she is certain the world will end before that. <br>
<br>
